  "diary": "Started the day the usual way—coffee and scrolling through Discogs, hunting for a mint copy of that Talk Talk album I've been after. The bus ride to Pioneer Square felt good with my podcast playing. Work was solid but heavy; had a couple of tough sessions where I could really feel the weight of what these kids are carrying. Took refuge at Café Solstice around lunch, sat in the AC and just... breathed for a minute.\n\nThe afternoon was all paperwork and follow-ups, the necessary stuff that keeps the machine running. I deliberately took the long route home to avoid the Pride chaos downtown—nothing against it, just felt like staying quiet today. Made an early dinner, checked on my fermentation vessel, and spent the evening in the best way: called Marcus, listened to some records, let the day settle. By evening I was reading with vinyl on low, feeling that particular peace you get when the world outside is busy and you're exactly where you need to be.",
  "thought_process": "I think I needed today to be gentle on myself. Work was emotionally taxing—two of my clients are in difficult spots and I carried that with me. I chose to skip the Pride festivities even though I usually love the energy; something about the noise and crowds felt like too much after being present for people all morning. The fermentation project and vinyl routine aren't just hobbies—they're how I process and reset. Calling Marcus was important too; I needed connection but on my own terms, in my own space. The route choice around Capitol Hill wasn't avoidance exactly, more like honoring what my body needed. By evening my mood had shifted from drained to grounded.",
